      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:63:21",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " أَمِيرَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) كَانَ لَا يَرَى الْحَبْسَ إِلَّا فِي ثَلَاثٍ رَجُلٍ أَكَلَ مَالَ الْيَتِيمِ أَوْ غَصَبَهُ أَوْ رَجُلٍ اؤْتُمِنَ عَلَى أَمَانَةٍ فَذَهَبَ بِهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abdul Rahman Bin Al Hajjaj, raising it, ",
          "(It has been narrated) that Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> would never imprison anyone except regarding three – a man who consumed the property of the orphan, or usurped it (property), or a man who was enstrusted upon a trust, so he went away (absconded) with it’."
        ]
      }
    }
